                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="ogtnotes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="ogt_1">
                            
<p>Mr van Gogh’s birthday on 8 February <ref target="let066.xml">(66)</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
                </listAnnotation>
                <listAnnotation xml:lang="en" type="notes">
                    
                        <note n="1" xml:id="note-t-1">
                            

<p>Vincent is referring to the so-called ‘text of the day’ (a lesson), an edifying text printed on calenders and in booklets for the pious to reflect upon.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p>
  1 Thess. 5:24.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

<p>Biblical.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="4" xml:id="note-t-4">
                            

<p>
  Exod. 3:14.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="5" xml:id="note-t-5">
                            

<p>This refers to Vincent’s application for a position in Scarborough (Great Britain), which he mentions in <ref target="let070.xml">letter 70</ref> (cf. FR b2233).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="6" xml:id="note-t-6">
                            

<p>In his last letter Vincent had asked Theo for a copy of <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_63"/><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_512">Andersen</rs>’s <hi rend="italics"><ref target="biblio.xml#lit_63">Vertellingen van de maan</ref></hi> (<ref target="let068.xml">see letter 68</ref>).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="7" xml:id="note-t-7">
                            

<p>It is not known to whom this refers, though it is possibly the person mentioned in <ref target="let043.xml#l-12">letter 43, ll. 12-13</ref>.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="8" xml:id="note-t-8">
                            

<p>
  Ps. 23:6; the text differs in a number of places from the King James version.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="9" xml:id="note-t-9">
                            

<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_787">Tersteeg</rs> will have discussed Vincent’s dismissal with his <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_524 bio.xml#_526">parents</rs> in Etten. Mrs van Gogh had already informed Theo: ‘You know that Mr Tersteeg has been here, I believe he also knows a great deal about it, about Vincent. We were pleased to see him’ (FR b2231, 5 February).</p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
